    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Bell-shaped jars, placed open-end down on a base and usually sealed, for display or storage of artifacts, natural specimens, dried flower arrangements, figurines, objets d'art, or other decorative items. For bell-shaped glass covers used to protect living plants, use "bell glasses (horticultural containers)."</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
